title: The 1955 Teacher Supply and Demand Report
items.abstract: <jats:p> The 1955 Teacher Supply and De mand Report is the eighth annual study of teacher supply and demand in the United States which has been conducted under the sponsorship of the National Commission on Teacher Education and Professional Standards. This report was prepared by the NEA Research Division in cooperation with the Commission. The 1955 report, like each of the pre ceding ones, was under the immediate supervision of Ray C. Maul. Dr. Maul is Assistant Director of the NEA Re search Division. </jats:p><jats:p> The Commission expresses its appre ciation to the Research Division and to Dr. Maul for their cooperation in the preparation of this important report. </jats:p><jats:p> The 1955 report is published exclu sively in the Journal of Teacher Educa tion. </jats:p>
